&lt;p&gt;Are you passionate about being at the forefront of the ever-evolving digital advertising industry? Do you thrive on proactively enabling agency partners, driving adoption, and helping agencies deliver measurable results for their clients?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Agency Customer Success Manager at Smartly&lt;/strong&gt;, you will own and grow a portfolio of enterprise agency partners from day one. You’ll act as a trusted advisor, proactively guiding agencies on strategy, product adoption, and best practices across social and programmatic advertising. This role offers a front-row seat to the fast-paced online marketing ecosystem, with the opportunity to build long-term partnerships, influence product direction, and drive meaningful growth for both Smartly and our agency partners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do...&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the primary point of contact for agency partners, delivering an exceptional, value-driven customer experience and fostering long-term, collaborative relationships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take a proactive approach to agency success by identifying growth opportunities, anticipating challenges, and driving ongoing engagement and retention&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a subject matter expert in the Smartly platform, social advertising, and programmatic fundamentals, providing consultative guidance, best practices, and strategic recommendations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with &lt;strong&gt;Agency Sales&lt;/strong&gt; to develop and execute comprehensive agency development and enablement strategies that drive awareness, adoption, and expansion&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate cross-functionally with &lt;strong&gt;Onboarding, Technical Solutions, Product, Engineering, and Marketing&lt;/strong&gt; to align resources and execution in support of agency growth initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work hand-in-hand with Onboarding teams to design and deliver scalable training programs that enable agency teams to effectively use and adopt the Smartly platform&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and deliver agency enablement programs, workshops, and educational resources tailored to different agency maturity levels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain strong relationships with key industry partners, including&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Meta, TikTok, Snap, Pinterest, Google&lt;/strong&gt;, and other ecosystem partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the voice of the agency, gathering feedback and insights to help inform Smartly’s product roadmap and go-to-market strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to building a world-class Agency Customer Success organization by developing playbooks, sharing best practices, and continuously improving internal processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;We’re looking for someone who...&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul data-list-tree=&quot;true&quot; data-indent=&quot;0&quot; data-border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Has &lt;strong&gt;4+ years of experience&lt;/strong&gt; in Customer Success, Account Management, or a similar customer-facing role, ideally within ad tech, martech, or digital advertising&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Brings strong knowledge of&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;social advertising platforms&lt;/strong&gt; (Meta, TikTok, Pinterest, Snapchat, etc.), with &lt;strong&gt;programmatic advertising knowledge&lt;/strong&gt; as a strong plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Is highly empathetic, proactive, and customer-obsessed, with a genuine desire to help agency partners succeed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Has a results-driven mindset with a bias for action, ownership, and cross-functional collaboration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Can clearly explain complex concepts and translate data into actionable insights for agency stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Thrives in fast-paced, ambiguous environments and brings a self-driven, entrepreneurial spirit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Has excellent written and verbal communication skills and is comf

&lt;p&gt;Are you an Art Director with solid experience in leading paid social campaigns? Are you looking to include digital work for global brands in your repertoire? Are you interested in emerging technology (AI), data and creativity? Are you comfortable independently shaping conceptual ideas into fully developed social ad campaigns?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a visionary, creative technologist who can handle the everyday production for our global creative service clients. Aside from production, your role includes strategic planning as a client-facing creative partner. As a Mid-level Art Director and part of the Global Creative Service team, you will help our clients improve and plan their social advertising campaigns. You will consider the client’s current offering and partner with them to set the visual strategy going forward. In addition, you will have the chance to work closely with our developers to create fully automated creative tools on our platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re definitely looking for you, if you ...&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 5 years’ of experience at an ad agency, digital agency, or an in-house team of an online advertiser (e-commerce, mobile apps, or gaming a huge plus)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in creating tactical, direct response ads, as well as conceptual thinking and stunning branding&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of social media advertising, particularly Facebook, Instagram, Snapchat, Pinterest, Google &amp;amp; YouTube including all ad formats and placements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of video production, motion design and editing&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in communicating and advising advertisers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have a clear understanding of SaaS and scaled creative tools, tech and tactics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cross-functional mindset and experience in working with product managers and developers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong vision for branding and excellent eye for high-quality ads&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Art Director at Smartly.io, you will …&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Join Smartly’s Global Creative Service team that creates and runs scaled Paid Social advertising campaigns on behalf of top global advertisers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with the Global Creative Director in their mission to deliver scalable cross-channel, full-funnel creative campaigns, unlock new customers to grow team revenue, leverage in-house AI models and tools to build campaigns for our global client list, enable and evangelize partners by showing what’s possible with Smartly creative tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide the client in the style, visual strategy, and appearance of their digital advertising&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Consult advertisers on creative best practices across the digital media suite&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand data and be able to take action based on the performance of your creative work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Master the Smartly platform’s creative features (like templating, automating, and scaling) and leverage them in daily creative work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide product feedback on the usability of the creative functionalities in the Smartly platform&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with regional customer teams on new business pitches&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Smartly&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Smartly is the AI-powered advertising technology company transforming ad experiences for brands and their consumers. Our comprehensive advertising platform seamlessly integrates the capabilities of media, creative, and intelligence to power more than 800 billion impressions and generate more than 300 billion creatives annually, delivering tangible business outcomes for brands and advertisers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Smartly is the only company in the industry recognized as a Leader in The Forres

&lt;p&gt;This role sits at the intersection of Total Rewards, People Analytics, and HR technology. You&#39;ll help build and maintain the operational foundations of Smartly&#39;s compensation programs while using data, systems, and insights to improve how we make people decisions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working closely with the Global Total Rewards Lead, you&#39;ll own key compensation operations, maintain our global job architecture and Workday compensation data, deliver workforce insights, and identify opportunities to improve the way the People team works through automation, AI, and scalable processes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Do. . .&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation Operations &amp;amp; Systems&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support and administer Smartly&#39;s global compensation programs, including market pricing, offers, promotions, internal moves, job evaluations, and annual compensation cycles in partnership with the Head of Total Rewards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage salary survey participation, compensation reporting, and analyses that support business decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze internal and external compensation data to provide recommendations that support equitable, competitive and consistent pay decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with HRBPs, Talent Acquisition, Finance, and business leaders to support compensation-related decisions and guidance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and continuously improve Smartly&#39;s compensation infrastructure, including Workday compensation configuration, salary structures, and the global job architecture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;People Analytics, Data &amp;amp; Insights&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain dashboards, reports, and workforce analyses that support compensation and broader People decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze workforce and compensation data to identify trends, gaps, and inconsistencies, and recommend actions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Validate and audit HR data, identifying data quality issues and resolving them proactively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improve reporting processes by standardizing outputs, increasing efficiency, and reducing manual work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Explore and implement innovative approaches—including AI, automation, and analytics—to improve how the People team works, enabling more scalable, data-informed decision making across the employee lifecycle&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improve data models, reporting structures, and analytics processes over time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Are Looking For . . .&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 2 years of experience in compensation, people analytics, HRIS, workforce analytics, or a similar analytical role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical skills with advanced Excel or Google Sheets experience and confidence working with large datasets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building dashboards or data visualizations using BI tools (e.g., Tableau, Power BI, Looker)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical and problem-solving skills with attention to detail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to translate data into clear insights and recommendations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently on well-defined problems and manage priorities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Naturally curious, with a continuous improvement mindset and an interest in simplifying processes through automation, AI, and better ways of working.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication skills with the ability to explain analytical concepts to both technical and non-technical audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable working with sensitive data and maintaining confidentiality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice to have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Workday (Core HCM and/or Compensation).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experie

&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Creative Director, Brand &amp;amp; Content&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Smartly is looking for a Creative Director to join our Brand &amp;amp; Content team and help shape how our brand comes to life across campaigns, content, events, digital experiences, and marketing initiatives. Reporting to the SVP of Brand &amp;amp; Content, this role combines creative leadership, people management, and conceptual thinking to create work that is distinctive, effective, and aligned with our business goals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll lead a team of designers, develop strong creative concepts, and partner across the business to bring Smartly&#39;s story to life. This role is ideal for someone who began their career in design, has evolved into a conceptual art director, and enjoys helping creative teams produce their best work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead, coach, and develop a team of designers, creating an environment where people can do their best work and grow their careers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop creative concepts and campaigns that strengthen Smartly&#39;s brand and connect with target audiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide clear creative direction and feedback throughout the creative process, from brief through final execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Brand, Content, Product Marketing, Communications, and other stakeholders to translate business objectives into compelling creative solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Elevate the quality, consistency, and effectiveness of Smartly&#39;s visual identity across all channels and touchpoints&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review and approve creative work, ensuring it meets strategic objectives, brand standards, and quality expectations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help establish and refine creative processes, workflows, and ways of working that enable the team to scale its impact&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay current on design, advertising, and cultural trends, bringing fresh thinking and new approaches to the team&#39;s work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Are Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leading and developing creative teams, including direct people management responsibilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong background in graphic design, brand design, visual communication, or a related creative discipline&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience as a conceptual Art Director, with a portfolio that demonstrates strong campaign thinking and creative problem-solving&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to translate strategy, messaging, and business goals into engaging creative concepts and visual storytelling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong design craft and a deep understanding of typography, layout, visual systems, and brand identity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience partnering with cross-functional stakeholders and navigating feedback from multiple audiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication, presentation, and collaboration skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to balance creative excellence with practical business outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with consumer-facing brands or B2C marketing is preferred, but not required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in technology, SaaS, or high-growth environments is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Offer You&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Five weeks paid time off (PTO), 11 company paid holidays, unlimited sick days&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Generous healthcare packages &amp;amp; mental health benefits&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;401K plus matching &amp;amp; equity grants for all new Smartlies&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Wellness benefit &amp;amp; learning reimbursement opportunities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Volunteer time off days &amp;amp; company donation matching opportunities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And so much more…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The base pay range for this position is as mentioned below

