&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Meet your Recruiter: Get to know each other and learn about working at Smartly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Meet the Hiring Manager: Gain deeper insights into the role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical Interview: Engage in an interactive discussion around Systems Design and Architecture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leadership Skills: Final discussion will be focusing on

&lt;p&gt;Are you passionate about building next-generation products with LLMs and generative AI? Do you want to work on technology that’s transforming how brands connect with people? Join our Meta team as an Engineering Manager!&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our mission is to build the leading AI-first platform for full-funnel conversational commerce in messaging channels, combining performance marketing with deep audience insights. This means creating features that help marketers easily craft, adapt, and optimize high-performing ads and enabling more meaningful, creative, and effective conversations between brands and their audiences.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We are technology agnostic and always strive to choose the best tools for the job. On the backend, our favoured stack is Node.js in combination with TypeScript usually coupled with PostgreSQL and RabbitMQ. On the front-end side of things, React with TypeScript is the flavour du jour.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our engineering teams consist of both product specialists and engineers, and alongside the lead engineer you will take the lead in delivering products and features in the right time with right content and brilliant quality. As an Engineering Manager, you will be in charge of getting the best out of people, through coaching, 1:1s, helping them build a development plan and in general removing blockers from the team&#39;s path.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This team owns the &lt;strong&gt;Meta offering&lt;/strong&gt;, one of the most critical and widely used platforms in our ecosystem. Meta powers a large share of our customer workflows and operates at significant scale, requiring high standards for reliability, performance, and data integrity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of this team, you will lead and contribute to &lt;strong&gt;key architectural and technical decisions&lt;/strong&gt;, focusing on system performance, large-scale data processing, robust validation, and seamless integration with the Meta APIs. The work directly impacts how customers experience and trust our platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will collaborate closely with a &lt;strong&gt;dedicated Product Manager&lt;/strong&gt;, guide a &lt;strong&gt;well-balanced engineering team&lt;/strong&gt; ranging from Junior to Staff level, and regularly engage with &lt;strong&gt;Meta engineers&lt;/strong&gt; to ensure strong alignment, best practices, and forward-looking solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead an autonomous Fullstack development team. Lead by example.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate team every day life. Enable them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Care about your team members&#39; growth and development. Go far together.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tackle ambitious technical problems and add your mark to our Engineering culture. Help us grow.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
